flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn already appended audit truth into downstream-consumable audit truth plus durable audit references"]
    G2["Keep this path narrower than audit append and narrower than archive preservation"]
    G3["Answer how authoritative audit truth becomes consumable by the rest of the platform in durable, referenceable way"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not raw runtime traffic and not the decision itself"]
    E2["The entry is the append-only audit truth that already exists after the decision chain has closed its audit-append requirement"]
    E3["The run-process is explicit that decision truth, action/outcome truth, and append-only audit evidence are all already committed"]
    E4["The audit surface purpose is already to append authoritative audit and lineage truth for the real-time lane"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Decision and action truth"]
    R2["Append-only audit truth"]
    R3["Audit-topic handoff"]
    R4["Downstream operational and evidence consumers"]
    R5["Durable audit refs and evidence surfaces"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Run identity"]
    C2["Decision and action lineage"]
    C3["Policy, bundle, config, and release identifiers"]
    C4["Durable by-ref evidence surfaces that later consumers will follow rather than infer"]
    C5["Every cross-plane output carries the policy, bundle, config, and release identifiers required for replay and audit"]
    C6["Origin-offset and by-ref evidence contracts remain authoritative"]
    C7["So this path carries more than an audit message; it carries the traceable reference structure that lets later consumers use audit truth safely"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats audit exists and audit is consumable and referenceable as two different truth boundaries"]
    L2["The system is not saying once the audit surface writes, later consumers can figure things out however they want"]
    L3["There is a dedicated handoff from append-only audit truth into explicit audit publication and durable evidence/reference surfaces"]
    L4["The audit surface, archive surface, and topic handoff are separated by purpose rather than blurred together"]
    L5["That is strong A-level design signal"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["The publication side is concretely seated on the audit topic"]
    S2["The copied baseline wired graph shows the audit surface publishing lineage audit into that topic"]
    S3["The topic is transported by MSK"]
    S4["The downstream case and evidence-consuming side is attached to that audit lane"]
    S5["The durable-reference side is concretely seated on the platform's pinned evidence substrate"]
    S6["Object storage remains the durable truth, evidence, and archive substrate"]
    S7["By-ref evidence contracts remain authoritative"]
    S8["So the path has both named bus boundary and named durable evidence substrate"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform wants the hot path to be explainable later and wants downstream operational work to consume audit truth, not guesses"]
    Y2["The audit and lineage framing exists so important decisions can be reconstructed and explained later"]
    Y3["The case escalation path explicitly begins from RTDL decision and audit outputs"]
    Y4["The cross-plane provenance law ensures those outputs carry the identity needed for replay and audit"]
    Y5["So the current design is trying to guarantee that audit truth is not only written, but actually propagated in a form the rest of the platform can trust"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The topic continuity contract shapes where audit publication happens and who owns it"]
    X2["The audit topic is the named handoff surface, with the audit surface as producer and downstream operational/evidence consumers on the other side"]
    X3["The append-only truths law shapes what kind of audit truth may be published at all: it must remain append-only"]
    X4["The by-ref evidence law shapes how later consumers are supposed to follow evidence: by durable references, not by informal reconstruction"]
    X5["The provenance law shapes what must survive the handoff: policy, bundle, config, and release identifiers for replay and audit"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds one more explicit boundary after audit append"]
    T2["That costs extra structure: an audit topic contract, consumer ownership boundaries, durable evidence/reference surfaces, and provenance fields that must survive publication"]
    T3["But that cost buys something important: later case-handling, evidence, and reporting surfaces do not need to reverse-engineer audit history from raw runtime traces or archive files alone"]
    T4["They can consume explicit audit handoff"]
    T5["The design chooses clear cross-plane ownership and reconstructability over a simpler but blurrier model of append once and let everyone else scrape it"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still decide, act, append audit truth, and later archive event history"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to how downstream operational work sees audit truth as an input"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to how evidence and reporting sinks consume audit truth"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to where durable audit references come from"]
    N5["It loses a clean answer to how downstream consumers avoid reconstructing the audit story from scattered internal stores"]
    N6["That would weaken A immediately because the system would have audit append but no explicit owner for the distribution and durable referencing of that audit truth across planes"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Audit truth is no longer only appended inside the audit surface"]
    O2["It is now published and referenceable for downstream consumers and evidence surfaces"]
    O3["Append-only audit truth comes first; publication and reference distribution happen after that"]
    O4["Durable evidence refs remain the authoritative thing being pointed to rather than being replaced by the topic itself"]
    O5["Owned outcome: explicit audit publication and durable reference surface"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for turning appended audit truth into consumable audit publication and durable references"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the handoff is explicit: named topic, named producer, downstream consumer side, and named evidence laws"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in the audit topic plus object-storage-backed durable evidence surfaces"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>this path is governed by append-only truth, by-ref evidence, and provenance laws"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the platform already knows downstream consumers must not invent their own audit truth, which is why the handoff boundary is explicitly owned"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>append-only audit truth becomes explicit downstream handoff and durable reference structure instead of remaining trapped inside one runtime surface"]
  end

